text.section:
A person applying for a permit pursuant to this section shall:
Have knowledge of archaeology, paleontology or history as qualified in subsection (1) of this section;
Provide a detailed statement to the state archaeologist giving the reasons and objectives for excavation or removal and the benefits expected to be obtained from the contemplated work;
Provide data and results of any completed excavation, study, or collection at the first of each calendar year;
Obtain the prior written permission of the owner if the site of the proposed excavation is on privately owned land; and
Carry the permit while exercising the privileges granted.
